The father of late musician, Sonny Okosun, has passed away 14 years after his son’s death. Okosun, who was known as the leader of the Ozzidi band, died on May 24, 2008 at 61 after a battle with a terminal ailment. The Nation reliably gathered that the late Okosun’s father died at 102 in the Ogba area of Lagos.   How ladies can have lasting relationships, by Naira Marley     Unlimited LA: My encounter with police during Sean Tizzle’s…     LASU begs Bella Shmurda to return back, complete degree…   He has since been buried. The family of the late Okosun confirmed to The Nation the passing away of their father as well as his burial. - Advertisement - Why I don’t follow anyone ob Instagram, by Jim Iyke